ure==\n[[File:Mr Peanut Sculpture on Bench at Atlantic City 01.jpg|thumb|Sculpture of Mr. Peanut seated (left) on a bench in Atlantic City, NJ, August 2006. The sculpture was later removed.]]\n* The artist Vincent Trasov, dressed as Mr. Peanut, ran as a [[joke candidate]] in the 1974 [[Vancouver]], British Columbia civic elections.<ref>{{cite news|last=Milroy|first=Sarah|title=Mr. Peanut's lasting impact on Vancouver|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/art-and-architecture/mr-peanuts-lasting-impact-on-vancouver/article4574604/|accessdate=August 19, 2013|newspaper=The Globe and Mail|date=September 28, 2012}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category}}\n* [https://www.planters.com/mr-peanut Planters.com: History of the Planters Nut]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Peanut}}\n[[Category:Food advertising characters|Peanut, Mister]]\n[[Category:Corporate mascots|Peanut, Mister]]\n[[Category:Fictional food characters]]\n[[Category:Fruit and vegetable characters|Peanut, Mister]]\n[[Category:Kraft Foods brands|Peanut, Mister]]\n[[Category:Mascots introduced in 1916]]\n", "name_user": "2601:204:c404:47f0:584a:6275:e772:7aa6", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Right name)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mr._Peanut"}
